{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":737,"text":"I was one of those kids that, every time I got in the car,"},{"time":4088,"text":"I basically had to roll down the window."},{"time":7031,"text":"It was usually too hot, too stuffy or just too smelly,"},{"time":11243,"text":"and my father would not let us use the air conditioner."},{"time":13597,"text":"He said that it would overheat the engine."},{"time":16354,"text":"And you might remember, some of you,"},{"time":18002,"text":"how the cars were back then, and it was"},{"time":19902,"text":"a common problem of overheating."},{"time":22268,"text":"But it was also the signal that capped the use,"},{"time":26288,"text":"or overuse, of energy-consuming devices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30710,"text":"Things have changed now. We have cars that we take across country."},{"time":33749,"text":"We blast the air conditioning the entire way,"},{"time":36910,"text":"and we never experience overheating."},{"time":38486,"text":"So there's no more signal for us to tell us to stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41473,"text":"Great, right? Well, we have similar problems in buildings."},{"time":47091,"text":"In the past, before air conditioning, we had thick walls."},{"time":50557,"text":"The thick walls are great for insulation. It keeps the interior"},{"time":53236,"text":"very cool during the summertime, and warm during the wintertime,"},{"time":56754,"text":"and the small windows were also very good because"},{"time":59154,"text":"it limited the amount of temperature transfer"},{"time":61745,"text":"between the interior and exterior."},{"time":64212,"text":"Then in about the 1930s, with the advent of plate glass,"},{"time":68084,"text":"rolled steel and mass production, we were able"},{"time":71480,"text":"to make floor-to-ceiling windows and unobstructed views,"},{"time":74930,"text":"and with that came the irreversible reliance on"},{"time":78656,"text":"mechanical air conditioning to cool our solar-heated spaces."},{"time":85237,"text":"Over time, the buildings got taller and bigger,"},{"time":88341,"text":"our engineering even better, so that the mechanical systems"},{"time":90982,"text":"were massive. They require a huge amount of energy."},{"time":94856,"text":"They give off a lot of heat into the atmosphere,"},{"time":97615,"text":"and for some of you may understand the heat island effect"},{"time":100815,"text":"in cities, where the urban areas are much more warm"},{"time":104325,"text":"than the adjacent rural areas,"},{"time":107275,"text":"but we also have problems that, when we lose power,"},{"time":110529,"text":"we can't open a window here, and so"},{"time":113290,"text":"the buildings are uninhabitable and have to be made vacant"},{"time":116104,"text":"until that air conditioning system can start up again."},{"time":119752,"text":"Even worse, with our intention of trying to make buildings"},{"time":123807,"text":"move towards a net-zero energy state, we can't do it"},{"time":128792,"text":"just by making mechanical systems more and more efficient."},{"time":131159,"text":"We need to look for something else, and we've gotten ourselves a little bit into a rut."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134937,"text":"So what do we do here? How do we pull ourselves and dig us"},{"time":139188,"text":"out of this hole that we've dug?"},{"time":142039,"text":"If we look at biology, and many of you probably don't know,"},{"time":144948,"text":"I was a biology major before I went into architecture,"},{"time":148604,"text":"the human skin is the organ that naturally regulates"},{"time":152993,"text":"the temperature in the body, and it's a fantastic thing."},{"time":156429,"text":"That's the first line of defense for the body."},{"time":159044,"text":"It has pores, it has sweat glands, it has all these things"},{"time":162253,"text":"that work together very dynamically and very efficiently,"},{"time":165671,"text":"and so what I propose is that our building skins"},{"time":168175,"text":"should be more similar to human skin,"},{"time":171824,"text":"and by doing so can be much more dynamic, responsive"},{"time":175936,"text":"and differentiated, depending on where it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179192,"text":"And this gets me back to my research."},{"time":181125,"text":"What I proposed first doing is looking at a different material palette to do that."},{"time":186435,"text":"I presently, or currently, work with smart materials,"},{"time":189346,"text":"and a smart thermo-bimetal."},{"time":191065,"text":"First of all, I guess we call it smart because it requires"},{"time":193977,"text":"no controls and it requires no energy,"},{"time":196707,"text":"and that's a very big deal for architecture."},{"time":199370,"text":"What it is, it's a lamination of two different metals together."},{"time":202184,"text":"You can see that here by the different reflection on this side."},{"time":206058,"text":"And because it has two different coefficients of expansion,"},{"time":209533,"text":"when heated, one side will expand faster than the other"},{"time":212830,"text":"and result in a curling action."},{"time":216367,"text":"So in early prototypes I built these surfaces to try to see"},{"time":220073,"text":"how the curl would react to temperature and possibly allow"},{"time":224266,"text":"air to ventilate through the system,"},{"time":227371,"text":"and in other prototypes did surfaces where the multiplicity"},{"time":230600,"text":"of having these strips together can try to make"},{"time":233081,"text":"bigger movement happen when also heated,"},{"time":237155,"text":"and currently have this installation at the Materials &amp; Applications gallery"},{"time":241219,"text":"in Silver Lake, close by, and it's there until August, if you want to see it."},{"time":244705,"text":"It's called \"Bloom,\" and the surface is made completely"},{"time":247603,"text":"out of thermo-bimetal, and its intention is to make this canopy"},{"time":251643,"text":"that does two things. One, it's a sun-shading device, so that"},{"time":255460,"text":"when the sun hits the surface, it constricts the amount of sun passing through,"},{"time":259470,"text":"and in other areas, it's a ventilating system,"},{"time":262839,"text":"so that hot, trapped air underneath can actually"},{"time":264992,"text":"move through and out when necessary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268870,"text":"You can see here in this time-lapse video that the sun,"},{"time":273001,"text":"as it moves across the surface, as well as the shade,"},{"time":275747,"text":"each of the tiles moves individually."},{"time":278223,"text":"Keep in mind, with the digital technology that we have today,"},{"time":280735,"text":"this thing was made out of about 14,000 pieces"},{"time":283748,"text":"and there's no two pieces alike at all. Every single one is different."},{"time":288477,"text":"And the great thing with that is the fact that we can calibrate"},{"time":290989,"text":"each one to be very, very specific to its location,"},{"time":294988,"text":"to the angle of the sun, and also how the thing actually curls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299934,"text":"So this kind of proof of concept project"},{"time":302740,"text":"has a lot of implications"},{"time":304704,"text":"to actual future application in architecture,"},{"time":308404,"text":"and in this case, here you see a house,"},{"time":310909,"text":"that's for a developer in China,"},{"time":313342,"text":"and it's actually a four-story glass box."},{"time":316086,"text":"It's still with that glass box because we still want that visual access,"},{"time":319923,"text":"but now it's sheathed with this thermo-bimetal layer,"},{"time":323805,"text":"it's a screen that goes around it, and that layer can actually"},{"time":326270,"text":"open and close as that sun moves around on that surface."},{"time":330298,"text":"In addition to that, it can also screen areas for privacy,"},{"time":334860,"text":"so that it can differentiate from some of the public areas"},{"time":337156,"text":"in the space during different times of day."},{"time":339748,"text":"And what it basically implies is that, in houses now,"},{"time":343011,"text":"we don't need drapes or shutters or blinds anymore"},{"time":346428,"text":"because we can sheath the building with these things,"},{"time":348595,"text":"as well as control the amount of air conditioning you need inside that building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354162,"text":"I'm also looking at trying to develop some building components for the market,"},{"time":357551,"text":"and so here you see a pretty typical"},{"time":360040,"text":"double-glazed window panel, and in that panel,"},{"time":364771,"text":"between those two pieces of glass, that double-glazing,"},{"time":367698,"text":"I'm trying to work on making"},{"time":369875,"text":"a thermo-bimetal pattern system"},{"time":371944,"text":"so that when the sun hits that outside layer"},{"time":374616,"text":"and heats that interior cavity, that thermo-bimetal"},{"time":379260,"text":"will begin to curl, and what actually will happen then"},{"time":382036,"text":"is it'll start to block out the sun"},{"time":384339,"text":"in certain areas of the building,"},{"time":386213,"text":"and totally, if necessary."},{"time":388154,"text":"And so you can imagine, even in this application, that"},{"time":390662,"text":"in a high-rise building where the panel systems go"},{"time":393339,"text":"from floor to floor up to 30, 40 floors, the entire surface"},{"time":398106,"text":"could be differentiated at different times of day"},{"time":400296,"text":"depending on how that sun moves across and hits that surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405755,"text":"And these are some later studies that I'm working on"},{"time":408574,"text":"right now that are on the boards, where you can see,"},{"time":410838,"text":"in the bottom right-hand corner, with the red, it's actually"},{"time":414179,"text":"smaller pieces of thermometal, and it's actually going to,"},{"time":416457,"text":"we're trying to make it move like cilia or eyelashes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421703,"text":"This last project is also of components."},{"time":424185,"text":"The influence -- and if you have noticed, one of my"},{"time":428042,"text":"spheres of influence is biology -- is from a grasshopper."},{"time":431618,"text":"And grasshoppers have a different kind of breathing system."},{"time":434225,"text":"They breathe through holes in their sides called spiracles,"},{"time":437627,"text":"and they bring the air through and it moves through their system to cool them down,"},{"time":441117,"text":"and so in this project, I'm trying to look at how we can"},{"time":444499,"text":"consider that in architecture too, how we can bring"},{"time":446681,"text":"air through holes in the sides of a building."},{"time":449347,"text":"And so you see here some early studies of blocks,"},{"time":452320,"text":"where those holes are actually coming through,"},{"time":454833,"text":"and this is before the thermo-bimetal is applied,"},{"time":458553,"text":"and this is after the bimetal is applied. Sorry, it's a little"},{"time":461252,"text":"hard to see, but on the surfaces, you can see these red arrows."},{"time":464460,"text":"On the left, it's when it's cold and the thermo-bimetal"},{"time":467638,"text":"is flat so it will constrict air from passing through the blocks,"},{"time":471240,"text":"and on the right, the thermo-bimetal curls"},{"time":473280,"text":"and allows that air to pass through, so those are two different"},{"time":476826,"text":"components that I'm working on, and again,"},{"time":478642,"text":"it's a completely different thing, because you can imagine"},{"time":480954,"text":"that air could potentially be coming through the walls"},{"time":483681,"text":"instead of opening windows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486562,"text":"So I want to leave you with one last impression about"},{"time":489250,"text":"the project, or this kind of work and using smart materials."},{"time":493630,"text":"When you're tired of opening and closing those blinds"},{"time":496810,"text":"day after day, when you're on vacation"},{"time":499803,"text":"and there's no one there on the weekends to be turning off and on the controls,"},{"time":503842,"text":"or when there's a power outage, and you have"},{"time":506197,"text":"no electricity to rely on, these thermo-bimetals"},{"time":509218,"text":"will still be working tirelessly, efficiently"},{"time":513216,"text":"and endlessly. Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":516522,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}